
Copy and paste these values in `.vimrc` file under HOME directory and vim must
be installed in the system, then `VIM` editor will provide a good look.
If `vim` is not installed, then the file is `.exrc` which would have few similar
functinality embeded into `vi` command, like `vim` command.

```
$ cat .vimrc
set bg=dark
set autoindent ruler
set expandtab ts=2 sw=2
set backspace=indent,eol,start
set nu cursorcolumn cul
set colorcolumn=80
$
```

Anothe way:-
Select the a paragraph in visual mode and then select `gq` which would set
the paragraph in wrap mode.
